cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a new certification authority authorization (CAA) resource record for the domain name system (DNS) and its impact on security.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the adoption of a new technology and its implementation in software systems.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the DNS and its impact on internet security.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper discusses the impact of a new technology on the security of online networks.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses the implementation of a new technology in distributed systems.
